I wanted to order for pickup. Neither app was working from my computer. I called the shack, and she denied it wasn't working. So, she ignored my problem. I tried again, after closing my browser for the fifth time. I was charged on my credit card, but it said my order didn't go through. Since I was charged, I walked to the store. There was no order and the maskless woman I spoke to on the phone told me that the message from Citibank that I get every time I make an online order, to tell me of charges, meant that my order did not go through. I wanted a sandwich; if the person in the store is so uncooperative, they can keep their sandwiches. I now have to dispute the charge for food I did not get. There is no reason to pay a fee to an outside company, when you are picking up your delivery.

So I grew up in Miami Florida, the second home of Cuban food. I was raised on the cuban style sandwich, with all the special aspects of it from the simplicity of its ingredients blended perfectly with the all important Cuban Bread. Since leaving, I have yet to see a sandwich done right... Until now. I can say that by far, this place matches easily some of the best cuban restaurants in Miami, and in some ways even tops them. I cannot claim it is the best in New York, but if you want a taste of what cuban food truly is, there is no better place I can recommend. Please get either the classic Cubano or the Streak as both are extremely authentic and delicious. I am frankly blown away by this place, makes me feel like I'm home.
